1.title: High Hopes
1.plot: Julie muses about high hopes, excited that Nathan is moving back to Australia. Donna continues with Logan. Buzz is the new addition to Rafter Electrical. Ted gets lost.

2.title: First Time for Everything

5.title: Reality Checks
5.plot: Nathan travels to London to track down his wife, Saskia and their son.

6.title: Manning Up
6.plot: Matt is despairing about his musical career, until Buzz gets a mate in a rising band to let him fill in when his guitarist is ill. Carbo enjoys his healthy sex life, but looks forward to fatherhood even more, and Retta secretly decides to go back on the pill. Nathan is exhausted, doing just too much with tireless baby Edward, but won't let Julie 'meddle'. Ted's dementia gets much worse, mistaking people for deceased ones from his younger days, with incidents like kicking Crabo's dog ad kissing his wife.

7.title: Taking Stock
7.plot: Jackson is miserable, feeling neglected by both parents. When Dave, the only reliable father figure, whose coaching works wonders, even turned the knave nobly protective of Cooper, prepares to leave on a long bush tour, something snaps. Coby is finally nearing the end of his prison term, but the visit from Frankie which her new room-mate, Matt, calls likely falls trough. Carbo looks forward to fatherhood too much to care about his birthday party, thus a real surprise while he planned a luxury suite. But finding out she's back on the pill spoils the party and spells ...

8.title: Damage Control
8.plot: Coby finally enjoys a visit from Frankie, although she's non-committal, yet afterwards she smashes Matt's hope to become her permanent house-mate and more intimate friend. Dave discovers that Jackson vandalized his minivan, blames father Buzz and instructs him to step up as father. Ted's latest amnesia episode includes driving off with Ruby to the zoo and getting arrested for trying to enter his former home. Still Julie feels too guilty to admit her father needs to go to a rest home, as he suggested months ago.

9.title: Role Reversals
9.plot: Jackson admits his vandalism to startled father Buzz. Carbo's new job is too exhausting to remain a stud in bed. After bad 'advice' from same-gender mates to play hard to get, Matt still ends up together with Emma. New restaurant chef Gary Edwards is quickly fired again by control-freak Donna, but a staff strike forces her to ask him back and he senses she's erotically tempted. Ted's latest nocturnal escapade ends in ER, so in his next clear spell he empowers Dave and reluctant Julie to commit him to residential care. Alas, they discover Internet poker inadvertently ...

10.title: Head vs. Heart
10.plot: Jackson's claim that neither part-time parent actually loves him brings Buzz to offer him a permanent home with him, on best behavior. Matt is so nervous when offered a recording session with the rising band that he messes it up, but ends up doing great with his own songs. Despite Julie sabotaging their own sale, the house is soon sold. Ted keeps forgetting about his thus affordable move to the rest home, but cooperates in lucid moments. Cook Gary Edwards and fellow staff have a surprise for Donna in the netball tournament she pressed female friends into.

11.title: Centre of the Universe
11.plot: Cody is finally released from jail. he finds Dave packing, as the house is sold. When Nathan's warning finding an affordable house is nearly impossible proves true, they resign to renting. Ben visits to 'help pack' and say goodbye to his childhood home, but also finds grandpa Ted doesn't even recognize him. Jackson and Buzz delight Dave with a surprise: his van, completely restored with Carbo's expert help. Nathan ends up accepting Carbo's offer to move in with him. Trish, now under a guru's spell, commandeers the Rafters to a bizarre party, catered by Gary at Donna's.

12.title: Packing Up the Rafters
12.plot:

1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Dave Rafter was looking forward to a 'second youth', alone again with his wife Julie, after daughter Rachel and lately successful son Nathan's marriages and 'immature' adult son Ben moved out - to help next-door Greek neighbor mate Nick 'Carbo' Karandonis house-sit his parents' home, only neither knows how to run a household. The house-mate the boys take in is the very nurse, who David felt humiliated by after an overdoses of Viagra to celebrate his re-won freedom. Then things go really wrong: Ron Barrett's firm, where the parents work, downsizes: Dave is kept only ...

2.title: Playing a Googly
2.plot: Dave still finds his new situation stressing: barely can he cope with giving up his electrician job, or the fact that his wife dumps her father on him - the father wanders through their house as silent as a ghost, only Dave finds out his 'unmanly' secret. Fortunately Ben's new nurse house mate convinces him she'll keep Dave's own exposure secret. Preventing Nathan becoming a rival rooster in dad's roost is hard enough - then daughter Rachel arrives. She opens up only to her mother, yet once Dave steps-up as dad finds it worth a bloody nose being beaten by her addicted...

3.title: She Ain't Heavy
3.plot: Ben enjoys living 'free' without his parents, despite the empty fridge and total mess. Realizing nurse Melissa is a guy-like house-mate only makes her more attractive, so mates Ben and Nick are suddenly rivals - parading macho and undressed - while warning each-other she's off-limits. Meanwhile only Ben can look out for sister Rachel, who's moved back home, fleeing abusive alcoholic husband Daniel. Daniel warns her he won't let her go - Rachel hits the bottle herself. Ben ends up abused by both feminists as somehow Neanderthal misogynist for barking off a gay pass in ...

4.title: How Did We Get Here?
4.plot: Nathan Rafter recounts how, in the past 18 months, his dreams seem to have come true and then fall apart again. First Sammy Westaway becomes his date and lover, then she turns out to be the daughter of real estate baron Tony Westaway, ideal for a young agent like him. It goes wrong when the honeymoon is canceled as Nathan's grandmother had a fatal cardiac arrest during the wedding, and Sammy forbids him to accept a lucrative job from her dad. Within months her shopping addiction exhausts their credit, so they move into his parents' place.

5.title: Lines of Communication
5.plot: Julie worries incessantly about the financial strain of supporting the entire family as Dave struggles to get referrals for his electrical contracting business. Meanwhile, Ben is uncomfortable with keeping a secret about Rachel from his family.

6.title: Facing Demons
6.plot: After grandpa finds a dirty tape, Rachel tells him how she instantly fell for Daniel Griggs at her first job in advertising. At first he charmed the whole Rafter family but soon proved to be a hopeless substance addict - Rachel doesn't quite manage to break up with him. Now the family knows his own secret, grandpa decides to move back home and face his nosy neighbors.

7.title: Self Made Man
7.plot: Nathan Rafter hid the invitation to his rich father-in-law's 50th birthday party from his 'humble' suburban family. When it gets out, everyone blames him. Nathan's wife Sammy insists on organizing the party instead of her mother Trish. Nathan's mother Julie, finally with a reason to dress up worries she has nothing fit to wear. Sister Rachel 'punishes' Nathan by inviting his suave private school mate Oliver as her date so Nathan's 'well-born' cover is blown. Ben and Carbo surprise their mother (in a good way) twice. Tony offers a penthouse to give the couple a new ...

8.title: Taking the Lead
8.plot: Ben's drunken one-night stand with Melissa threatens to destroy their potential relationship and so to give her space he seduces Lauren but she turns out to be just what he didn't need. Meanwhile, Dave's past catches up with him when he sees a television interview with his former band mate Steve Wilson and Carbo develops a crush on Chrissy.

9.title: Suburban Boy
9.plot: Dave Rafter had been willing to forget about his 'once promising' rock career, but Steve Wilson who continued playing after their sole hit, asks him along for a one-time-only easy tour, which he accepts impulsively. The kids learn about their dad's writing fame, and Nathan finds it most helpful to close a real estate deal with the band's fan magnate Fred Mackie. Bennie stands in as the wine waiter. However something goes wrong. Dave deals with his unfinished business drastically.

10.title: All in the Planning
10.plot: Carbo keeps courting Julie's colleague Chrissey Merchant and must babysit his own sister's kids - Agysilas proves quite a handful for him and Ben. Hotel guest Nick Leigh, investor Venderbergh's man, makes Sam jump through hoops to set her bumbling straight, then courts her. Nathan put his foot down to stop luxuries being bought that they can't afford. Rachel bumps into her ex, Daniel, just when she discovers she's expecting. Although she can't hide it from Melissa, Ben even thinks it's 'their' pregnancy, and the family opposes a panic abortion.

11.title: Away from It All
11.plot: Julie plans a quality time weekend away in an old-fashioned beach cabin with Dave, grandpa and the 'kids'. Nathan 'can't get away from work' so he can have the house alone with Sammy, but she ruins this rare chance by nagging him about leaving his cellphone on and walks out. Despite her views against all men, Rachel nearly pulls hunky biker Ewan, who tours Australia as long his terminal MS allows. Ben's nurse-mate Melissa has a bad prawn allergy reaction and refuses to talk about her estranged family. Carbo 'hosts' Chrissy back home, but she "can't" commit.

12.title: Removing the Block
12.plot: Shortly before Christmas Dave wants more quality time for Julie and him, so he enforces domestic chores roster. Alas that exposes everyone to a practical breakdown, a mysterious stench and Rachel's macrobiotic 'cooking'; to her amazement next door proves housekeeping can work well, even with kid brother Ben and his cahoot Nick. Nathan feels there's just no time left after work, and that's not working either. Grandpa tries Friend Finders, but is he really ready for dating? Ma misses mothering. Chrissey makes up with Carbo.

13.title: Smiling Through the Pain
13.plot: The Rafters feel their bodies let them down. Ben is ashamed an armed hold-up made him literally piss his pants, yet the suggestion of therapy is even scarier. Dad Dave's dental maintenance costs $6,000 but he can't afford without accepting a job with his ex-colleague Warney. Also dealing with his gang lands him in a nightclub and trouble ensues. He still gets the surprise birthday party that he really feels too old for. The girls discover Rachel's yoga motivation, studly guru Vishnu, but ma finds taking the mikey out of her literally painful.

14.title: A Mother's Radar
14.plot: Sick of not getting anytime alone, Nathan and Sammy arrange a romantic rendezvous at a vacant property but are discovered by Nathan's boss Carl who promptly fires him. However, Nathan cannot tell Sammy what has happened so he lies to her and his family as he goes about trying to get another job whilst getting jealous at the re-appearance of Sammy's ex-fiancé Owen Matheson. Rachel brings her relationship with Vishnu out in the open but Vishnu's openness upsets Dave. Later Chrissy tells Julie that Vishnu is spreading it around amongst all the female yoga participants - ...

15.title: Natural Justice
15.plot: Nathan continues his search for a job opportunity in property and finds out that his old colleague Damien has been bad-mouthing him. Ben goes on jury duty and meets Cat and ends up bringing her back to meet Carbo and Melissa but Mel doesn't take to her at all. Ben and Cat help Nathan get back at Damian and Nathan finds a purpose in organising Dave's business. Cat moves in to Ben's old room when he moves in with Mel but is Mel right to have doubts about her?

16.title: Having It All
16.plot: Rachel tries to move on with her life after George gives her an inspiring boom but gets mixed results but it does net her a potential new older mate. After appointing Nathan as his new manager to sort out his work life Dave finds that it is not running as smoothly as he had hoped.

17.title: Changes
17.plot: Ted ventures back into the dating world but goes a little too far with his double dates. Dave becomes concerned about Rachel's new man Rob as Rachel gets to know Rob's two sons and Kat arouses suspicions from Chrissie and Melissa but Ben takes her side. Will it be to his detriment?

18.title: House of Cards
18.plot: Ben faces a gut-wrenching dilemma. Should he tell Melissa the truth about his drunken night with Kat? He talks to Kat who promises not to tell Melissa but can he trust her especially when Kat and Mel start to become friendly? Meanwhile, after some prompting from Julie Dave spices up his marriage and organises a strangers rendezvous with Julie at a bar. Later Julie organises a follow-up date in a motel room. Elsewhere, Sammy and Nathan's relationship becomes strained when he discovers she's lied to him about how she got the money to fly to New York for her friend's ...

19.title: Over the Moon
19.plot: Rachel's boyfriend Rob's enthusiasm for playing happy families startles Rachel and causes her to break up with Rob. Will Ben get another chance with Mel after fate puts her back in his path and Julie has concerns about her health which doesn't help when Carbo's mother Rita suggests it could be the start of the menopause. Meanwhile, Carbo proposes to Chrissie which disgusts his mother and prompts him to move in with Chrissie.

20.title: Losing the Touch
20.plot: Julie's hormones are playing havoc with her usual ability to give sound advice to her family. Ben decides to declare his love to Mel on national television with comic results and Rachel reveals that she is moving out to live with her best friend Libby - but is this really the best decision? Elsewhere, Sammy returns home from New York with expensive presents for all the family, but Nathan is not impressed. Sammy takes it bad and decides to move home shortly before an investigation begins into her father's personal fortune.

21.title: What a Difference a Year Makes
21.plot: As Julie remembers her mother's anniversary along with Ted and the family Nathan tries to re-connect with Sammy on their first wedding anniversary. But later Julie is in for a huge shock and it is Ted that takes the brunt of her shock but he mistakenly thinks it's because she doesn't like his new lady friend Marjorie. Elsewhere, Ben tries to win Melissa back but he's in for a shock when her ex-fiancé Shannon turns up looking for her. Meanwhile, Sammy tries to get her dad to face-up to wrong he has done to all his investors.

22.title: Don't Know What You've Got 'Til It's Gone
22.plot: Dave and Julie tackle the shocking news that Julie is to become a mum for the fourth time. But the risks at Julie's age causes grave concern for Dave and he urges her to think about it as he'd rather have her than not have her. Rachel reveals her painful abortion secret to Julie and Melissa's ex Shannon tries to get to see Melissa but Ben is not making it easy. Meanwhile, Ted finds it easier to talk to Marjorie about his family than his own family and Sammy's mother leaves her dad and goes off to London on holiday.

1.title: Look Into My Eyes
1.plot: Bonnie Bright, a psychic/sandwich vendor gets Julie worried about her family especially when her predictions start to come through one by one. Meanwhile, Ben tries too hard to win Mel back.

2.title: Dodging the Issue
2.plot: Nathan receives a job offer from Tim Connelly and Dave feels betrayed when he thinks about taking it. Julie believes Dave is being ripped off by Warney but Dave refuses to see that it could be true until he discovers the evidence for himself. When Nathan decides to take the job Dave offers Nathan's position to Chrissie who lost her job because of Warney. Elsewhere, Ben pushes his luck too far in trying to compete for Melissa's affections over a new doctor and discovers that he has a heart condition. This prompts Dave to think about looking for his real parents who ...

3.title: Living by the List
3.plot: Ben is determined to get a promotion to Bar Manager at the Bar but must compete against another more qualified manager to get the coveted job. Rachel goes on a number of blind dates, most of which have been set up by Libby, but the dates continuously put her in the path of crude, but handsome, rugby player Jake Barton. Nathan's new job does not live up to the expectations promised. Meanwhile, Julie's attempts to get time with the kids falls flat at each hurdle.

4.title: Glittering Prizes
4.plot: Rachel tries her hardest to resist Dave's new electrician Jake's flirting but finds herself falling for his charms just as Libby begins to have feelings for George. Ben is devastated by Mel's revelations that she is dating Luke and Nathan receives and unexpected job offer from Steve Wilson and his girlfriend Layla and quits his job with Tim. Is it the right decision?

5.title: Brave New World
5.plot: An older married customer at the flower shop gets to know Carbo very well until he realises she is stalking him. Meanwhile, Dave and Julie anxiously await the results of the test on their unborn baby and Dave does not take it well that their baby could be born with Downs Syndrome. Elsewhere, Nathan starts he new but eventful job with Layla.

6.title: Little Arrows
6.plot: Ted and Marjorie's romance continues to blossom until he meets her opinionated lesbian daughter Susannah and her pregnant partner Abbey. Rachel gets trapped in a building that is being renovated with Jake where her animosity towards him eventually turns to heated passion. After a drinks promotion at the club leads to a female clubber being drugged Ben is accused of the crime. Fearing that he will be charged with a crime he didn't commit Mel helps to prove that he wasn't responsible.

7.title: Belonging
7.plot: Sammy's mother Trish returns to Australia and promptly has a breakdown and also has nowhere to live so she heads to the Rafters. Melissa moves back into Ben and Carbo's home - but is she back for good? Elsewhere, Rachel fights her attraction to Jake after their night of passion but will she succumb to Jake's charms again?

8.title: What's in a Name?
8.plot: Dave begins to have nightmares about a dog after Ben's adopted dog keeps making a beeline for him. Is the nightmare telling him he has to address the issue of finding out who his parents are? Julie persuades her boss to give Trish a job but Trish manages to make Julie look bad as she looks good in the bosses eye. Jake sets out to prove to Rachel that they have a future as a couple. Meanwhile, Summer gives birth to a boy and steals Julie's preferred name.

9.title: Naked Visions
9.plot: Rachel takes some artistic photographs of Julie as her body changes but not all the family wants to see the results. Dave gets close to Ben's dog Doorknob and is distraught when he is badly injured. He later receives his birth certificate and finds out his mother's name was Rachel Warne and his father was listed as unknown. Meanwhile, Ben proposes to Mel but doesn't get the instant yes he was hoping for.

10.title: Ready to Catch You
10.plot: Dave finally tells the rest of the family about this early childhood and his mother and buoyed by their enthusiasm he goes seeking further information but is devastated when the agency reveal his mother doesn't want to see him. However, his mother Rachel turns up at his door but leaves in tears without talking to Dave. Meanwhile, Rachel meets Jake's family - his cheeky brother Alex who has cerebral palsy and this acerbic mother Grace who takes an instant dislike to Rachel. The following day Jake has a workplace accident and Grace tells Rachel to stay away from her son...

11.title: Power Play
11.plot: Dave's mother Rachel engineers an electrical fault ruse to get him to come and see her. She tells him that his father died very young and that she was hospitalised in a psych unit and that was the reason she gave him up. He invites her to dinner with the family and whilst she charms the rest of the family Dave isn't impressed particularly when he finds out that she travelled a lot whilst he was growing up. Meanwhile, Rachel brings Jake to the launch of 'Rampant' where she has also booked a suite for their first romantic night together. Jake overdresses in a dinner ...

12.title: Out of Left Field
12.plot: Carbo's former childhood neighbour, Artemis from Lesbos in Greece, comes to stay with Carbo's mother Rita. But Artemis has a wild side and it takes all Carbo's wits to keep her away from men she has hooked up with on Facebook. But unknown to him this is Rita's plan - for him and Artemis to become a couple. Meanwhile, Sammy interviews her ex Owen and Layla for her first journalistic assignment and finds out about Nathan and Layla's kiss. Elsewhere, Rachel still hasn't heard from Jake, Dave considers getting a vasectomy and Julie faints when out with Rita and Chrissie.

13.title: Blurring the Lines
13.plot: Artemis prepares for her first day of work at the Boat Club but Carbo worries when she becomes friends with fellow bar worker Lexi. Meanwhile, Nathan's attraction to Layla begins to spin out of control until he can no longer deal with it and finally seduces her after promising Sammy he will stay out of Layla's way. Elsewhere, Dave rehires Warney, much to Chrissy and Julie's disgust, and who makes a beeline for Sammy's mother. Chrissy finds herself becoming more and more attracted to Dave.

14.title: First Instinct
14.plot: Dave's mother Chel is overwhelmed by a surprise birthday party thrown in her honour by the Rafters. At the end of the party Rachel discovers marks on Chel's arm which Chel brushes off but which Rachel feels are drug marks. Later, Chel confesses that she is HIV Positive and has been for over 20 years. Ben and Mel come down with food poisoning after eating smoked oysters at the birthday party but afterwards Mel finally accepts Ben's marriage proposal. Jake and Rachel continue to remain strained but he encourages her to talk to his mother who has apparently changed ...

15.title: It's My Party
15.plot: Dave throws the party of all parties for Ben and Melissa's engagement which distracts him from news that Chel is attending the renal unit several times a week. Nathan panics when he hears that Steve is coming back early but despite his attempts to gag Layla she proceeds to tell Steve that she slept with Nathan which alerts Sammy and causes her to confront Nathan at the party. Meanwhile, Melissa's parents refuse to come to the party because they believe she won't make it to the alter. Elsewhere, Carbo finds out about Chrissie's crush on Dave.

16.title: Mr Fix-It
16.plot: Dave and Nathan are at loggerheads because of Nathan's actions towards Sammy and the disappearance of Chel is not helping. So Ted starts by offers Nathan advice on saving his marriage to Sammy and also going on a trip to find Chel. Nathan tries to talk to Sammy but it doesn't go well so he asks Ben to invite her to stay with Ben in the spare room hoping that it will help. Jake and Rachel get romantic and go on a date to a rock gig and he gets caught by Dave sneaking out the next morning.

17.title: Putting the House in Order
17.plot: Rachel sees Sammy having lunch with her old boyfriend Owen and hatches a plot with Jake to get Sammy and Nathan together. Meanwhile, Julie goes back to consult psychic Bonnie about her earlier prediction and Chrissie avoids Julie because of her attraction to Dave but then tells her that she is quitting and moving to Queensland to be with a man. But Julie soon realises the truth. Elsewhere, Ben and Melissa announce that they are getting married in a simple ceremony a month later.

18.title: Space Junk
18.plot: Rachel meets her ex-boyfriend Daniel at the advertising campaign launch of Rampart of which Jake is also involved. She soon discovers that flowers that she thought Jake sent were actually from Daniel. However, after Jake arrives late with his brother Alex, the Rampart bosses complain and Daniel takes it out on Alex, much to Jake's disgust who quits the entire project. Elsewhere, Sammy makes the big step to move back in with Nathan but finds it hard to become intimate with him again. Chel gives Nathan some prescription cannabis to get him back on track with Sammy.

19.title: A Small, Traditional Affair...
19.plot: It's Ben and Mel's wedding weekend and it starts off well with Ben on his bucks night and Mel having an unofficial hen/pajama party. But the stripper hired for Ben turns out to be Kat who tells him he's not good enough for Mel. The following day Mel's parents Pat and Linda arrive from Perth and Pat echoes much of what Kat had already said to him - and so he flees. Nathan finds him and manages to talk him into going ahead with the wedding. Ben arrives late, but after all it was a non-traditional wedding, and they marry. Chel turns up at the wedding and Julie forces her...

20.title: Only a Heartbeat Away
20.plot: Carbo is lonely with Ben and Melissa gone on honeymoon so he ends up on a bender with Warney and drunkenly allows Warney to move in fearing Ben and Mel would want their own place. Meanwhile, whilst on honeymoon Ben and Mel are propositioned by a swingers couple. Elsewhere, Chel and Dave finally talk and she tells him more about his dead father Tom Jennings. Wanting to find out more Nathan and Dave do an Internet search for his burial site but instead find out that it appears he never died and is very much alive and living in rural New South Wales.

21.title: Unlimited Options
21.plot: After getting knocked back on the job front Nathan heads out into rural country to look for his grandfather Tom Jennings but gets a shock when he finds out he's in jail. Later, Nathan and Sammy go out to a casino with Trish and her new partner Andrew Malouf where Nathan gets a taste for gambling and Warney makes a scene in trying to get Trish back. The following day Trish calls around with a cheque for Warney which he won at the casino after declaring his love and it's good news for Carbo, Ben and Mel when he decides to move out. Elsewhere, Rachel throws Julie a baby ...

22.title: Nativity Play
22.plot: Nathan wins $14,000 at the casino with the chips he kept and tells Sammy to look for an apartment as they now have enough to move out. But thinking he can improve his winnings he goes back and promptly loses it all. Knowing he has stuffed up he tries to talk to Julie but Chel won't let him and offers to give him $5,000 but he's never to go near a casino again. Julie moves into Carbo's air-conditioned home but goes into labour just after Dave goes for his vasectomy. Elsewhere, whilst at a restaurant with Jake and his mother, Rachel witnesses Jake having a fit and then ...

1.title: The Blank Page
1.plot: The Rafter clan welcomes its latest addition, named Ruby Louise. Nathan is encouraged in his desperate refusal to accept Sammy has left him for good this time. Her mother Trish ends up convincing Ted that she moved to London with an ex, having closed the marriage chapter completely. Jake must face his semi-crippled condition for half a year.

2.title: Saturday Night, Sunday Morning
2.plot: Julie's confidence as a mum takes a beating when baby Ruby resists Julie's attempts to breastfeed. Newly single Nathan hits the town with Carbo, and Ben can't help feeling left out. Jake's becomes over-protective as his mum begins seeing someone. Mel's loyalty is tested when she runs into Sammy, who begs her not to tell Nathan she's still in town.

3.title: To Tell or Not to Tell
3.plot: Dave's dilemma over whether to reveal that his birth-father is alive leads to a roadtrip to meet his mysterious other family. Melissa is finding Sammy's secret increasingly difficult to keep from Ben. Rachel becomes the green-eyed monster when Jake's client, an attractive housewife, seems to be coming on to him.

4.title: A Good Husband
4.plot: Ben wants to make up with Mel by treating her to romance for their anniversary, so he books a balloon surprise trip. Nathan can't talk Carbo out of treating the happy couple to a second-hand water-bed, which proves as leaky as the very idea. Jake finally gets to meet his mother Grace's first lover in years, Doug, but Rachel can't convince him there's no ground for his obvious suspicions. Another stressed call from Sammy worries Mel so badly that Ben ends up canceling their trip, which is welcomed surprisingly warmly.

5.title: The Invisible Man
5.plot: Carbo is surprised when Mel suddenly objects to unhygienic bathroom borrowing and sharing. Ben works out the real problem is Sammy, still calling her in secret, and gets her to agree they'll tell Nathen she's not overseas. Ted stands up to a gang of abusive street girls, but thus gets Chel injured and once again she resists help from Dave. After lonely neighbor crone Lumbscone dies unnoticed, Ted arranges for a seniors check-up system and a self-defense program run by Ben's burly bar bouncer.

6.title: Home Matters
6.plot: Jake and Rachel plan to move out, although their ideas of a suitable home hardly square. Jake had sort of accepted Grace's lover Doug, but discovering about him and big brother moving out proves to much for Alex, who has unexpectedly returned from New Zealand. Rachel starts realizing how attached she's to home with its comforts and memories. Ben and Mel consider Carbo's home is decorated too much to his parents's taste, so they spend some wedding gift cash on introducing a hunters theme.

7.title: Simple Needs
7.plot: Nathan is about to sign his divorce papers, so Ben finally musters the courage to tell him Sammy is still in Sydney. They meet but she crushes his hope for a reconciliation. Carbo's recent Internet celebrity status now yields a teenage stalker girl, Georgia, which terrifies him and ultimately Ben. Julie comes up with an embarrassing 'solution'. Jake notices that Rachel is jealous of the 'princess' fuss about new youngest sibling Ruby. Dave is exhausted by the 'new' mother but still catches up.

8.title: Rites of Passage
8.plot: The Rafter clan gathers to welcome Ruby. Even devout orthodox Carbo can't convince them to hold a proper christening, so Rachel recommends an alternative 'celebrant' for the park picnic and ceremony, which proves the worst part of her hopeless input. Jake is pleased to be invited with mother and brother, but Alex can't accept her boy-friend at home, for which Jake ultimately provides a startling alternative. Nathan has been approved medically as kidney donor for Chel, who is as reluctant as his parents, but also has to pass a psychological session, which makes him ...

9.title: The Price of Parenthood
9.plot: Coby spies on the Rafter house and reports in jail to his equally puzzled grandfather, Tom Jennings, who thinks that Nathan, resembling him, must be his illegitimate son. Carbo's stalker Georgia sees him and tells Julie. Dave decides to go visit his father with Nathan, Chel declines and isn't even remembered, reason enough for Dave to storm out. Jake installs himself and Alex in their new bachelor boys home, but Rachel refuses to keep visiting unless they clean to girl standards. Mel's 'house training' example inspires her nastily.

10.title: Out of the Comfort Zone
10.plot: Ben desperately tries to avoid sacking waitress Lexi, but owner Derek insists that's his duty as manager. Jake volunteers to babysit Ruby with Rachel, but she bails out, so Jake brings the baby to Ben and Mel, who prove naturals. Nathan tells Dave he will get to know grandpa Tom, at least after his kidney donation. Grandpa Ted recognizes Roger's daughter Hayley as the street punk who attacked him and Chel, and unlike her insists on informing the police. When Roger wants Ted's seniors club banned from the club, Ben stakes his job, although he craves a regular income ...

11.title: Lessons in Happiness
11.plot: Ben and Mel feel pressure mount now that people know they want offspring, even Julie's gift, a simple cookbook, adds to stress. After resuming rugby training, Jake has a third fit, so the doctor will diagnose epilepsy. Since it was at home, he wants to keep it secret for now, but Alex, who found him, is too scared and tells Rachel. Nathan and Chel get a donor kidney surgery date in two weeks. Rachel is in line for a promotion but secretly applies for a dream job with Paul Morgan's much bigger firm behind boss Lewis's back and without consulting Jake whom she would see...

12.title: Moments of Truth
12.plot: Just before his kidney donation, Nathan wants to make preparation, including letters 'just in case' for his loved ones, and visits Tom in jail lacking inspiration. Tom's invitation for Chel works, and he proves actually remembering their affair, to both's relief. Ben finds it hard to face any risk of losing his 'kid brother'. Carbo's bird-watching date is a fiasco, but being the erroneous victim of gay-bashing after delivering to a queer yields him another 'future bride', who in fact only wants him for her gay brother.

plot: Centres around Dave and Julie Rafter and their three children Rachel, Ben and Nathan. But home is a very welcome refuge for their children and when unforeseen problems loom, they return like a boomerang.::Anonymous

Electrician Dave Rafter and his wife, Julie, expected the house would feel empty and quiet as their children become adult. Although Ben is eager to move out, even when he gets his dream as he buddy, neighbor 'Carbo', starts minding his parents' house, Ben keeps raiding the fridge, dropping laundry and asking advice and help. His sister Rachel is a hopeless screw-up in every sense, unable to finish anything. Youngest Nathan actually gets a good real estate agency job and a rich, devoted partner, but even they face misfortune leading to the couple moving in with Dave.::KGF Vissers

A series that a lot of parents can relate to these day, just when Dave and Julie think they finally have the house to themselves to be able to enjoy some quiet time, family members need to move back in. Interesting to see the situations and challenges the family face and how they cope with them. Excellent Australian series, great actors and believable characters.
